不行      那我就自己去巴黎
I can't. Then I'll go to Paris without you.

165
00:08:31,245 --> 00:08:33,480
你好 伯纳 对 是我
Hello, Bernard... Yes, it's me...

166
00:08:33,647 --> 00:08:35,749
听着 明天的行程不得不取消
I'm going to have to cancel tomorrow.

167
00:08:36,650 --> 00:08:38,785
斯旺西和纽卡斯尔
Swansea and Newcastle.

168
00:08:39,920 --> 00:08:42,389
明天是我妻子的结婚周年纪念
It's my wife's wedding anniversary tomorrow...

169
00:08:43,590 --> 00:08:44,758
也是你的
It's yours too!

170
00:08:44,925 --> 00:08:48,028
对 实际上也是我的 对 就是这样
Yeah, and mine too actually. Yes, it is.

171
00:08:48,529 --> 00:08:50,430
什么真巧? 别傻了
Coincidence? Don't be silly.

172
00:08:50,931 --> 00:08:53,600
总之 明天我去巴黎 最终决定
Anyway, I'm going to Paris tomorrow and that's final.

173
00:08:54,268 --> 00:08:57,671
是的 我是说过 但这次是最终的
Yes, I said that before, but this time is final!

174
00:08:58,772 --> 00:09:01,308
你要使出全身解数摆平
You'll just have to cope as best as you can.

175
00:09:02,409 --> 00:09:03,477
没错
Yes?

176
00:09:04,111 --> 00:09:06,046
对 很明确
Yes... definitely...

177
00:09:06,813 --> 00:09:08,115
对
Yes...

178
00:09:08,315 --> 00:09:09,550
明白了?
Is that clear?

179
00:09:10,117 --> 00:09:11,251
好的
Right!

180
00:09:11,685 --> 00:09:13,187
我们去巴黎
We're going to Paris.

181
00:09:13,487 --> 00:09:15,856
不 我要去斯旺西和纽卡斯尔
No, I'm going to Swansea and Newcastle.

182
00:09:20,394 --> 00:09:22,996
今晚在电视上看到我了?     我倒是看到有个人像你
See me on TV tonight? I saw somebody who looked like you.

183
00:09:23,163 --> 00:09:24,998
这话的意思是?      什么也不是
What's that meant to mean?     Nothing.

184
00:09:25,165 --> 00:09:27,868
弗兰克说我成了公务员的传声筒
Frank says I've become a Civil Service mouthpiece.

185
00:09:28,035 --> 00:09:29,236
是啊      "是啊"是什么意思?
Yes.          What do you mean, yes?

186
00:09:29,403 --> 00:09:31,238
就是是啊      你是说你同意?
Well... yes.           You mean you agree?

187
00:09:31,405 --> 00:09:33,841
当然      "当然"是什么意思?
Of course.       What do you mean, of course?

188
00:09:34,007 --> 00:09:37,311
你还不如雇人去讲话 没准比你讲的好呢
You could have hired and actor to say it all foryou.

189
00:09:37,477 --> 00:09:39,947
你何不用橡皮图章来签信件
And why not just sign your letters with a rubberstamp?

190
00:09:40,113 --> 00:09:42,516
或者让你的助理代劳
Orget an Assistant Principal to sign them foryou.

191
00:09:42,683 --> 00:09:44,084
反正就是他们写的
They write them anyway.

192
00:09:44,384 --> 00:09:47,187
我的信才不是助理写的呢
Assistant Principals do notwrite my letters!

193
00:09:48,088 --> 00:09:49,790
是副秘书写的
UnderSecretaries do that.

194
00:09:50,290 --> 00:09:52,192
我放弃申辩了 大人
I rest my case, my lord.

195
00:09:53,126 --> 00:09:56,497
你认为我成了傀儡?      是的 我认为是
You think I've become a puppet?      Yes, I do.

196
00:09:56,730 --> 00:09:59,633
也许该让芝麻街的猪小姐做你的工作 她至少比你漂亮
Get Miss Piggy to do yourjob. She's prettier.

197
00:09:59,800 --> 00:10:01,401
我不知如何是好
I don't knowwhat to do.

198
00:10:01,568 --> 00:10:03,704
我被工作困住了
I'm just swamped by the work.

199
00:10:04,404 --> 00:10:06,206
安妮 我真郁闷
Oh, Annie, I'm so depressed.

200
00:10:08,208 --> 00:10:10,310
既然我们不去巴黎
As we're not going to Paris,

201
00:10:10,444 --> 00:10:14,214
至少今晚去街角的饭店吃顿安静的晚餐
let's at least go out fora quiet little dinnertonight.

202
00:10:14,915 --> 00:10:16,049
我不能
No, I can't.

203
00:10:16,216 --> 00:10:18,719
伯纳要我今晚搞定三个红盒子
Bernard's told me to get through three boxes.

204
00:10:18,886 --> 00:10:20,854
什么叫伯纳要求你?
What do you mean, Bernard's told you?

205
00:10:21,054 --> 00:10:23,824
在《改革》做编辑的时候 你可不是这样的
When you edited "Reform" you were quite different.

206
00:10:23,991 --> 00:10:26,226
你走进去 吩咐底下人怎么做
You went in, you told people what to do,

207
00:10:26,426 --> 00:10:28,162
说你要什么 他们就准备什么
and you got what you wanted!

208
00:10:28,328 --> 00:10:31,465
你不先发制人就会被骑在头上
Eitheryou get them by the throat orthey get you by the throat!

209
00:10:31,632 --> 00:10:34,935
那段日子你撕毁多少文章?
Howmany articles did you tearup in those days?

210
00:10:35,068 --> 00:10:38,105
几十篇      那你现在撕毁过多少公文?
Dozens. And howmany official papers?

211
00:10:38,372 --> 00:10:41,108
这是不允许的      不允许?
I'm not allowed to! Not allowed to?

212
00:10:41,375 --> 00:10:45,245
亲爱的 你是大臣 可以为所欲为
Darling, you're the Minister, you can do anything you like.

213
00:10:49,416 --> 00:10:51,585
不 汉弗莱 弗兰克是对的
No, Humphrey, I've decided that Frank was right.

214
00:10:51,752 --> 00:10:53,053
鲍勃・麦肯齐也是
And Bob McKenzie too.

215
00:10:53,187 --> 00:10:55,856
国家数据库必须用其他的方式建立
The National Data Base has got to be organised differently.

216
00:10:55,989 --> 00:10:56,990
是的 大臣
Yes, Minister.

217
00:10:57,157 --> 00:10:59,193
确保安全措施到位
We want all possible built in safeguards.

218
00:10:59,359 --> 00:11:01,361
是的 大臣      立刻
Yes, Minister.      Right away.

219
00:11:01,528 --> 00:11:04,431
"立刻"的确切意思是?
What precisely do you mean, right away?

220
00:11:05,265 --> 00:11:06,733
就是马上执行
I mean right away.

221
00:11:07,234 --> 00:11:09,236
懂了 你是指马上执行 大臣?
I see, you mean right away?

222
00:11:09,736 --> 00:11:12,239
汉弗莱 确保到位     好的 大臣
Got it in one, Humphrey. Well, Minister...

223
00:11:12,406 --> 00:11:15,075
或许我该提醒您 我们还尚在内阁成立初期
We are still in the early months of this Government.

224
00:11:15,242 --> 00:11:16,710
还有许多工作...
And there's an awful lot to get...

225
00:11:16,877 --> 00:11:18,946
汉弗莱 资料库的规章必须现在更改
The Data Base rules have got to be changed. Now!

226
00:11:19,112 --> 00:11:22,416
可是您不能 大臣     不 我能 我是大臣
But you can't, Minister. Yes, I can, I'm the Minister.

227
00:11:22,649 --> 00:11:24,318
是的 大臣 您确实是
Yes, indeed you are, Minister.

228
00:11:25,052 --> 00:11:27,154
而且是一位卓越的大臣
And quite an excellent Ministerat that.

229
00:11:27,321 --> 00:11:29,323
汉弗莱 别奉承了
Nevermind the soft soap, Humphrey.

230
00:11:29,523 --> 00:11:32,826
我要让所有公民都有权利查阅自己的档案
I want all citizens to have a right to see theirown files

231
00:11:32,993 --> 00:11:36,663
我要立法惩治未经许可的违规查阅
and I want legislation to make unauthorised access, illegal.

232
00:11:37,231 --> 00:11:39,633
好的 大臣 就这么办     好极了
Very well. It shall be done. Good.

233
00:11:39,933 --> 00:11:43,203
但要立法授权公众采取法律行动
But the legislation necessary to give the public the right

234
00:11:43,370 --> 00:11:46,673
要通过十分繁杂的手续
to take legal action is extremely complicated

235
00:11:46,840 --> 00:11:50,043
还要耗费大量时间来起草
and would take considerable time to draft,

236
00:11:50,043 --> 00:11:51,612
宣传 颁布
promulgate and enact.

237
00:11:51,745 --> 00:11:55,349
公民查阅自己的档案无需立法 对吗
Legislation isn't necessaryfora citizen to see his own files, is it?

238
00:11:55,716 --> 00:11:58,185
是的     那就从这开始
No... Then, we'll startwith that.

239
00:11:58,352 --> 00:12:01,655
好吧 我们会争取快点实施 大臣
I suppose we could manage that slightly quicker,

240
00:12:01,788 --> 00:12:05,125
但还存在许多管理上的难题
but there's an awful lot of administrative problems as well.

241
00:12:05,292 --> 00:12:07,194
汉弗莱 先前对此肯定有过研究
This must have been examined before.

242
00:12:07,361 --> 00:12:10,197
多年前资料库就在筹备中
The Data Base has been in preparation foryears.

243
00:12:10,364 --> 00:12:13,000
肯定就此展开过讨论
There must have been discussions about it.

244
00:12:13,167 --> 00:12:16,069
确实有 大臣      达成的结论是?
Yes, indeed. What conclusions were reached?

245
00:12:18,772 --> 00:12:21,575
汉弗莱 达成的结论是?
Humphrey, what conclusions were reached?

246
00:12:22,843 --> 00:12:25,812
我的前任对此抱何态度?
What did my predecessor want to do about it?

247
00:12:26,079 --> 00:12:28,115
汉弗莱 你能听到我说的吗?
Humphrey, can you hearme?

248
00:12:29,750 --> 00:12:31,285
我必须守口如瓶
My lips are sealed.

249
00:12:32,052 --> 00:12:33,120
再说一遍?
I beg yourpardon?

250
00:12:33,287 --> 00:12:36,256
我不能公开先前的计划 大臣
I am not at liberty to reveal previous plans, Minister.

251
00:12:36,390 --> 00:12:37,424
为什么不能?
Why not?

252
00:12:37,624 --> 00:12:41,228
大臣 您愿意把您在办公室的一言一行
Would you like everything that you have said in this office

253
00:12:41,395 --> 00:12:44,364
都告知随后接任您职务的对手吗?
to be revealed subsequently to one of youropponents?

254
00:12:45,399 --> 00:12:46,466
明白 不
I see. No.

255
00:12:46,667 --> 00:12:50,504
我们不能给您对手政治弹药来对付您 反之亦然
We cannot give youropponents political ammunition against you.

256
00:12:50,771 --> 00:12:52,706
可我的前任汤姆・萨金特
But Tom Sargent was my predecessor.

257
00:12:52,906 --> 00:12:55,475
与我是一个党派的 他不会介意的?
It isn't a party political mattersurely?

258
00:12:55,642 --> 00:12:58,245
原则问题 大臣 不能公开
It's a matterof principle. It justwouldn't be...

259
00:12:59,413 --> 00:13:02,316
我明白 我们不能开这种...
I see and we don'twant to do anything thatwouldn't be...

260
00:13:02,483 --> 00:13:03,517
不行
No.

261
00:13:04,985 --> 00:13:07,154
打扰下 大臣     什么事 伯纳?
Oh, excuse me, Minister.      Yes, Bernard?

262
00:13:07,321 --> 00:13:08,889
小问题 大臣
A slight problem, Minister.

263
00:13:09,256 --> 00:13:11,024
由于反对的声浪
Because of the adverse...

264
00:13:11,191 --> 00:13:15,128
就是说 您的访谈并没有获得一致的赞同
not entirelyfavourable press reaction to your interview,

265
00:13:15,295 --> 00:13:17,998
其他频道想让您上他们的节目
the otherChannel wants you fortheirprogramme.

266
00:13:18,165 --> 00:13:19,266
拒绝     不去?
Say no.          No?

267
00:13:19,466 --> 00:13:20,934
是的 不去      好的 不去?
Yes, no.         Yes no?

268
00:13:22,002 --> 00:13:24,905
是的 拒绝 最终决定      要是您这么想
Yes, say no! That's final. Lf that's what you want.

269
00:13:25,072 --> 00:13:27,374
他们说了 就算您不露面 他们还会播出节目
But they would go ahead with the item

270
00:13:27,574 --> 00:13:30,310
那时候可就没人替您维护了
and nobody would be there to state yourcase.

271
00:13:30,477 --> 00:13:31,812
不去? 好吧 去
No? Okay, yes.

272
00:13:32,145 --> 00:13:33,614
不去 好吧 去
No, okay, yes...

273
00:13:34,882 --> 00:13:36,884
我懂您的意思      去
Oh, I see what you mean. Yes.

274
00:13:37,084 --> 00:13:38,385
最后的最终意见?
Finallyfinal?

275
00:13:38,986 --> 00:13:40,487
伯纳 谢谢
Thank you, Bernard.

276
00:13:41,688 --> 00:13:44,825
汉弗莱 安全措施的问题我该怎么说?
What am I going to tell them about safeguards. Humphrey?

277
00:13:44,992 --> 00:13:47,561
您可以提醒他们 大臣
Perhaps you could remind them, Minister,

278
00:13:47,728 --> 00:13:49,930
冰冻三尺非一日之寒
that Rome wasn't built in a day?

279
00:14:00,240 --> 00:14:01,375
汤姆
Tom.

280
00:14:02,109 --> 00:14:04,645
我的朋友     介意我坐下吗?
Oh, my dearfellow.        Mind if I join you?

281
00:14:04,811 --> 00:14:06,113
当然不
No, of course not.

282
00:14:06,647 --> 00:14:10,184
当反对党的滋味如何?
Well, how are you enjoying being in opposition?

283
00:14:10,651 --> 00:14:12,486
执政的感觉如何?
How are you enjoying being in Government?

284
00:14:12,653 --> 00:14:16,824
实际上并非如我期望那般 此刻就不是
Well, not as much as I expected, actually.Well, not at the moment.

285
00:14:17,424 --> 00:14:18,826
汉弗莱把你制服了?
Humphrey got you undercontrol?

286
00:14:19,159 --> 00:14:20,994
想做成点事情真难
It's so hard to get things done.

287
00:14:21,161 --> 00:14:23,964
你办成过什么事吗?      几乎没有
Did you manage to get things done? Oh, almost nothing.

288
00:14:24,798 --> 00:14:29,203
我直到选举来临才摸透了他的战术
When I did cotton on to his technique, there was the election.

289
00:14:29,403 --> 00:14:32,506
战术?       拖延战术
Technique? Stalling technique.

290
00:14:33,073 --> 00:14:35,676
拖延战术?       有五个阶段
Stalling technique? It comes in five stages.

291
00:14:36,176 --> 00:14:40,514
首先 他会跟你说内阁新建 尚有许多事务要处理
First, he'll tell you there's lots of things to be getting on with.

292
00:14:40,714 --> 00:14:42,916
他今早就是这么多我说的      当然了
He told me that this morning.      Quite.

293
00:14:43,383 --> 00:14:46,320
其次 如果你仍然坚持 他会这么说
Then, if you still persist, he'll say something like

294
00:14:46,487 --> 00:14:49,690
"好的 大臣 意图很好
"Ah, yes, Minister, I quite appreciate the intention,

295
00:14:49,857 --> 00:14:51,792
确实应该施行
certainly something ought to be done,

296
00:14:51,959 --> 00:14:55,095
但你肯定这是实施它的正确方式?"
but are you sure this is the rightway to achieve it?".

297
00:14:55,229 --> 00:14:56,663
我应该记下来
I must make a note of this.

298
00:14:56,830 --> 00:15:00,267
如果你还没有被唬住 他会改变立足点
Now, if you are still undeterred, he will shift his ground.

299
00:15:00,567 --> 00:15:05,272
从告诉你如何做转向何时做
He will shift from how to do it to when you should do it.

300
00:15:05,472 --> 00:15:06,907
他会这么说
I mean, he'll say,

301
00:15:07,307 --> 00:15:10,911
"大臣 现在不是恰当的时机
"Now, Minister, this is not the right time,

302
00:15:10,911 --> 00:15:12,446
出于各种原因"
forall sorts of reasons".

303
00:15:12,613 --> 00:15:15,349
大臣们就裹足不前了?      多数如此
And Ministers settle forthat?     Well, lots do.

304
00:15:15,516 --> 00:15:16,984
如果你没有放弃
And if you don't,

305
00:15:16,984 --> 00:15:19,386
他会说政策"拟定起来困难重重"
he'll say that the policy"has run into difficulties".

306
00:15:19,586 --> 00:15:23,557
比方说?       技术上 行政上 法律上
Such as?        Technical, political, legal...

307
00:15:24,324 --> 00:15:25,959
法律是最好的托词
Legal are the best sort.

308
00:15:26,126 --> 00:15:28,762
他会使其听起来玄乎其玄
He can make those totally incomprehensible.

309
00:15:29,129 --> 00:15:33,066
走运的话 这个战术会持续三年
And with any luck, this technique will have lasted forthree years

310
00:15:33,233 --> 00:15:35,802
到了最后阶段 他会告诉你
and you'll be at the final stage when he says:

311
00:15:35,969 --> 00:15:38,705
"大臣 下一届大选近在咫尺
"We're getting very close to the next general election.

312
00:15:38,872 --> 00:15:40,874
你能确保这项政策通过?"
Are you sure you can get this policy through?"

313
00:15:41,041 --> 00:15:43,010
三年 怎么能拖了三年?
Howhas it taken three years?

314
00:15:43,177 --> 00:15:46,547
因为你不督促 汉弗莱爵士是绝对什么也不会做的
Sir Humphrey will do absolutely nothing unless you chase him.

315
00:15:46,747 --> 00:15:48,682
而你偏偏还有一堆事情要做
And you've got fartoo much to do.

316
00:15:48,849 --> 00:15:52,386
你瞧 他们称之为"创造的惰性"
You see, it's what they call "creative inertia".

317
00:15:54,755 --> 00:15:57,791
你要设法通过什么政策?
What's the policy you're trying to get through anyway?

318
00:15:57,958 --> 00:16:00,928
我试着让国家综合数据库
I'm trying to make this National Integrated Data Base

319
00:16:01,094 --> 00:16:02,763
少些极权主义
a bit less of a Big Brother.

320
00:16:04,431 --> 00:16:06,200
原来是这么回事
Oh, is that what it is?

321
00:16:06,366 --> 00:16:09,169
他告诉你这是新政策 对吧?     是啊
He's told you it's all quite new? Well, yes.

322
00:16:09,336 --> 00:16:11,438
我的朋友 这项法案我们耗了几年
My dearfellow, we spent years on that.

323
00:16:11,605 --> 00:16:14,274
政府白皮书都写好了 可惜大选了
We had a White Paper when they called election.

324
00:16:14,274 --> 00:16:15,843
这些我都做过
I've done it all.

325
00:16:16,210 --> 00:16:19,079
那些行政麻烦呢?      全都解决了
And administrative problems? I've solved them.

326
00:16:19,546 --> 00:16:21,915
他告诉你不能看先前的文件?
And you couldn't see any of the previous papers?

327
00:16:21,915 --> 00:16:24,451
是的      不足为奇 他已经清盘了
yes No wonder. He's wiped the slate clean.

328
00:16:25,986 --> 00:16:28,288
知道他下一步会怎样吗?
D'you knowwhat his next move's gonna be?

329
00:16:28,455 --> 00:16:31,124
不知道      今晚给你几箱文件?
No. Howmany boxes have you got?

330
00:16:31,291 --> 00:16:33,427
3箱? 4箱?       5箱
Three? Four?      Five.

331
00:16:33,594 --> 00:16:36,230
