可我不理解 汤姆是反对党
But I don't get it. Tom's the opposition.

344
00:17:18,972 --> 00:17:20,607
他为什么告诉你这些?
Why did he tell you all this?

345
00:17:20,774 --> 00:17:24,278
反对党并不表示敌对      当然不 我犯糊涂了
The Opposition aren't the opposition. Of course not. Silly of me.

346
00:17:24,444 --> 00:17:27,548
他们只是这么称呼     他们不过是在野的反对党
They are called that. They're the opposition in exile.

347
00:17:28,515 --> 00:17:31,285
那些公务员才是在朝的反对党
The Civil Service are the Opposition in residence.

348
00:17:31,952 --> 00:17:35,656
汤姆说在第5个盒子的底部
Now then, bottom of the fifth box, Tom said.

349
00:17:35,856 --> 00:17:38,792
但就算你知道也无能为力
But you can't really do anything.

350
00:17:38,959 --> 00:17:40,093
无能为力?
Oh, can't I?

351
00:17:40,327 --> 00:17:42,763
资料库相关的文件汤姆都给我了
Tom's given me all his papers on the Data Base.

352
00:17:43,430 --> 00:17:44,998
三年的价值
Three year's worth!

353
00:17:45,332 --> 00:17:46,533
了不起
Marvellous!

354
00:17:49,837 --> 00:17:51,238
找到了
Found it.

355
00:17:51,505 --> 00:17:55,776
竟然被夹在长达80页的福利措施报告里
It had slipped into an 80 page report on Welfare procedures.

356
00:17:57,678 --> 00:18:00,080
"安全措施仍在讨论
"Safeguards still underdiscussion...

357
00:18:01,048 --> 00:18:03,016
计划悬而未决
programme not finalised...

358
00:18:03,550 --> 00:18:05,185
"不可草率行动
nothing precipitate...

359
00:18:05,686 --> 00:18:09,923
若无相左之指示 建议待发展再定夺"
failing instructions to the contrary, propose await developments".

360
00:18:10,090 --> 00:18:11,091
老一套
Typical!

361
00:18:11,225 --> 00:18:14,795
给汉弗莱打电话 说你不同意    我一早就会见他
Ring Humphrey and tell him. I'll see him first thing.

362
00:18:15,095 --> 00:18:17,798
现在就打给他     现在可是凌晨2点
Ring him now!             It's two o'clock.

363
00:18:17,965 --> 00:18:20,334
他正睡得香呢      要的就是这效果
He'll be fast asleep.            Exactly!

364
00:18:22,569 --> 00:18:23,604
安妮
Annie.

365
00:18:23,770 --> 00:18:26,106
凭什么他安稳入睡你却仍在工作?
Why should he be asleep and you're still working?

366
00:18:26,273 --> 00:18:28,575
他害你白白忙活 现在轮到你整整他
He's had you on the run. Now it's yourturn.

367
00:18:29,476 --> 00:18:31,278
我不能够这么做
I couldn't do that.

368
00:18:32,246 --> 00:18:33,480
他电话多少?
What's his number?

369
00:18:34,748 --> 00:18:37,951
何况材料在第5个盒子里 你根本无法早些看到
Itwas in the fifth box, you couldn't have got to it earlier.

370
00:18:38,152 --> 00:18:39,319
有道理
True.

371
00:18:56,870 --> 00:18:57,871
喂?
Yes?

372
00:18:58,038 --> 00:19:00,841
汉弗莱 这么晚打扰你真不好意思
Humphrey, sorry to ring you so late.

373
00:19:01,041 --> 00:19:04,278
我没破坏你晚餐的兴致吧?
I didn't interrupt you in the middle of dinner, did I?

374
00:19:05,813 --> 00:19:08,015
没有 晚餐早结束了
No, we finished dinner some while ago.

375
00:19:08,148 --> 00:19:09,716
现在几点了?
Oh, good. What's the time?

376
00:19:09,917 --> 00:19:11,351
凌晨两点
Er, two a.m.

377
00:19:12,085 --> 00:19:14,555
我的老天 出了什么大事?      没有 一切正常
Good God, what's the crisis? No. No crisis.

378
00:19:14,555 --> 00:19:15,756
我正在研究盒子
I'm going through my boxes,

379
00:19:15,756 --> 00:19:17,991
而且我知道你肯定也还在鞠躬尽瘁
and I knew you'd still be hard at it.

380
00:19:18,192 --> 00:19:21,195
对的 对的 埋头苦干
Oh, yes, yes, yes, yes. Nose to the grindstone.

381
00:19:21,361 --> 00:19:24,331
那好 我刚看到资料库的文件
Well, I've just come across this Data Base paper.

382
00:19:24,464 --> 00:19:26,466
您发现... 您看过了
Oh, you've found... you've read it!

383
00:19:26,967 --> 00:19:29,870
我得说这让我很不满
Thought I'd bettertell you I'm not happy with it.

384
00:19:30,037 --> 00:19:33,440
你将有幸为此另寻出路
You'll welcome an opportunity to work on something else.

385
00:19:33,607 --> 00:19:36,844
不介意我打电话给你吧     不 大臣 一点也不
You didn't mind my calling you? No. Not at all Minister.

386
00:19:37,110 --> 00:19:39,012
听到您的声音总是非常愉快
Always a pleasure to hearfrom you.

387
00:19:41,815 --> 00:19:44,952
糟了 我忘了告诉他内阁会议前来找我了
I meant to tell him to see me about it before Cabinet.

388
00:19:44,952 --> 00:19:46,386
现在别打给他
Don't ring him now.

389
00:19:47,154 --> 00:19:48,989
是啊 现在是晚了点
You're right, it is a bit late.

390
00:19:49,990 --> 00:19:51,825
让他先睡10分钟
Give him anotherten minutes.

391
00:19:57,231 --> 00:19:59,032
您最好速战速决
If you could be fairly quick.

392
00:19:59,199 --> 00:20:01,835
他10点要参加内阁会议     我可以马上解决
He does have Cabinet at 10.      I can be very quick.

393
00:20:02,002 --> 00:20:05,038
伯纳 "不行"是要对大臣说的最简洁的句子
The word "No" is one of the shortest in the language.

394
00:20:06,907 --> 00:20:10,077
抱歉来晚了 今早有许多公文要读
Sorry to be so late. Lots of reading to do this morning.

395
00:20:10,711 --> 00:20:12,946
伯纳 早安 谢谢 乔治
Good morning, Bernard. Thank you, George.

396
00:20:14,948 --> 00:20:17,584
汉弗莱 资料库的事
Now, Humphrey, the Data Base.

397
00:20:18,485 --> 00:20:20,287
你起草了安全措施的计划书了吗
Have you drafted yoursafeguards?

398
00:20:20,487 --> 00:20:22,956
大臣 我十分欣赏您的意图
Well, Minister, I quite appreciate your intention

399
00:20:23,123 --> 00:20:25,759
而且非常认同安全措施的必要性
and fully agree that there is need forsafeguards,

400
00:20:25,926 --> 00:20:27,427
但是
but is this

401
00:20:28,395 --> 00:20:31,532
这是实施它的正确方式吗?      是我的方式
the rightway to achieve it?        Well, it's my way.

402
00:20:32,132 --> 00:20:33,534
一个对上了
One.

403
00:20:35,602 --> 00:20:37,171
无论如何 我主意已定
That's my decision, anyway.

404
00:20:37,437 --> 00:20:41,208
出于各种因素 现在不是恰当的时机
Well this is not really the time forall sorts of reasons.

405
00:20:42,476 --> 00:20:43,844
两个
Two.

406
00:20:45,312 --> 00:20:46,847
现在正是时候
It's the perfect time.

407
00:20:47,147 --> 00:20:49,516
安全措施应该紧跟系统的步伐
Safeguards should be developed alongside systems,

408
00:20:49,683 --> 00:20:51,084
这是常识
that's common sense.

409
00:20:51,251 --> 00:20:55,355
之前我们已经有过各种尝试 实施起来困难重重
We tried all this before and we ran into all sorts of difficulties.

410
00:20:55,589 --> 00:20:56,757
三个
Three.

411
00:20:57,424 --> 00:20:58,592
比如?
Such as?

412
00:20:59,493 --> 00:21:02,529
例如技术上     不 没问题
Well, technical, for instance. No. No problems.

413
00:21:02,696 --> 00:21:05,833
我研究了 我们可以实施与美国国务院
We can use the same basicfile interrogation programme

414
00:21:05,999 --> 00:21:08,969
以及瑞士内政部一样的审核程序
as the U.S. State Dept. And the Swedish Ministry of the Interior.

415
00:21:09,403 --> 00:21:10,704
这个不成问题
No problems there.

416
00:21:11,104 --> 00:21:14,708
好吧 但行政上存在极大的麻烦问题
Yes, but there are also formidable administrative problems.

417
00:21:17,511 --> 00:21:19,513
各部门都会受到影响
And all departments are affected.

418
00:21:19,746 --> 00:21:23,484
跨部门委员会...     不不不 汉弗莱
An interdepartmental committee... No. No. No, Humphrey.

419
00:21:23,684 --> 00:21:27,721
我想你会发现 现行的安全手续足以胜任
You'll find that the existing security procedures are adequate.

420
00:21:27,888 --> 00:21:30,624
只需简单地完善 还有吗?
This is simply an extension. Anything more?

421
00:21:30,791 --> 00:21:34,027
还有 大臣     例如法律问题?
Well, yes, Minister. Legal problems, forexample?

422
00:21:36,630 --> 00:21:38,565
对 大臣      很好 很好
Yes, Minister.      Good, good.

423
00:21:38,732 --> 00:21:40,234
我们有法律权限吗?
Do we have the legal power?

424
00:21:40,267 --> 00:21:42,436
我可以帮你解答 我们有
I'll answer it. We have.

425
00:21:42,603 --> 00:21:45,606
工作人员的职权受到其协议的约束
All personnel affected are bound by theirstaff agreements.

426
00:21:45,772 --> 00:21:49,309
是的 但大臣 这将需要额外配备公务员
Yes, but Minister, there will be a need forextra staffing.

427
00:21:49,476 --> 00:21:53,213
你能让其在内阁和议会通过吗
Will you be able to get it through the parliamentary party?

428
00:21:53,347 --> 00:21:56,116
是的 我确定可以 还有其它问题吗?
Yes, I'm quite sure. Anything further?

429
00:21:56,283 --> 00:21:58,152
我看没了 我们可以着手去做了
I don't think so. We can go ahead then.

430
00:22:03,157 --> 00:22:04,558
你不吭声啊 汉弗莱
You're very silent.

431
00:22:04,725 --> 00:22:08,595
大臣 你似乎没意识到荆棘丛丛
You don't seem to realise the amount of work that's involved.

432
00:22:08,762 --> 00:22:11,064
难道你曾调查过安全措施的问题?
Haven't you examined safeguards before?

433
00:22:11,231 --> 00:22:12,733
在其他的内阁里?
Underanothergovernment?

434
00:22:12,866 --> 00:22:16,570
我记得在议会上有过类似答辩
I remembersome written answers to parliamentary questions.

435
00:22:17,171 --> 00:22:20,874
首先 我们说好的 这不能...
Well, in the first place as we've agreed that question is not...

436
00:22:21,408 --> 00:22:24,344
其次 即便有过调查
In the second place, if there had been investigations,

437
00:22:24,511 --> 00:22:26,814
其实要么没有 要么没必要
which there haven't ornot necessarily,

438
00:22:26,947 --> 00:22:29,416
要么我无权透露
orl am not at liberty to say whetherthere have,

439
00:22:29,616 --> 00:22:31,585
那就必然有过一个研究小组
there would have been a project team, which,

440
00:22:31,752 --> 00:22:34,054
其存在过与否 我无可奉告
had it existed, on which I cannot comment,

441
00:22:34,188 --> 00:22:36,623
即便存在过 也已经解散了
which would nowhave disbanded if it had existed

442
00:22:36,790 --> 00:22:38,826
成员已经各自回到曾经的部门
and the members returned to do theirdepartments,

443
00:22:39,026 --> 00:22:41,195
如果真的存在过这些成员的话
if indeed there had been any such members.

444
00:22:41,695 --> 00:22:43,397
或者也可能从没存在过
Ornot as the case may be.

445
00:22:44,231 --> 00:22:45,666
正是这样 大臣
Quite so, Minister. I want these safeguards

446
00:22:45,833 --> 00:22:48,635
汉弗莱 我要安全措施立即实施
made available immediately.

447
00:22:48,802 --> 00:22:51,171
大臣 根本不可能      可能
Minister, it is not possible.       It is.

448
00:22:51,305 --> 00:22:52,840
不可能      可能
It isn't.         It is.

449
00:22:53,006 --> 00:22:54,374
不可能      可能
It isn't.           It is.

450
00:22:54,508 --> 00:22:57,144
不可能     可能可能可能可能
It isn't.        'Tis, 'tis, 'tis, 'tis, 'tis, 'tis.

451
00:22:57,911 --> 00:23:00,481
大臣 只是提醒您 内阁会议在10点举行
Just to remind you, you have Cabinet at 10.00,

452
00:23:00,647 --> 00:23:02,749
1点参加英美协会
the Anglo American Society at one,

453
00:23:02,916 --> 00:23:06,119
傍晚接受"聚焦世界"的采访
and the "World in Focus" interview, this evening.

454
00:23:06,353 --> 00:23:07,554
连个吃饭的空都没有?
Can't you get me out of the lunch?

455
00:23:07,588 --> 00:23:09,756
很抱歉 大臣 已经对外通告过了
I'm afraid not minister.It's been announced.

456
00:23:09,923 --> 00:23:11,358
我想想 我以为我...
I see... I suppose I...

457
00:23:13,126 --> 00:23:15,729
你刚说什么 伯纳?     我们不能更改 大臣
What's that you just said? We can't get out of it.

458
00:23:15,896 --> 00:23:18,065
已经对外通告 已列入日程
It's been announced, it's in the programme.

459
00:23:18,932 --> 00:23:20,334
谢谢 伯纳
Thank you, Bernard.

460
00:23:21,435 --> 00:23:23,170
万分感谢
Thank you very much.

461
00:23:23,303 --> 00:23:24,838
大臣 为什么?
Forwhat, Minister?

462
00:23:25,973 --> 00:23:28,308
为一切 伯纳德
Foreverything, Bernard.

463
00:23:34,848 --> 00:23:36,316
聚焦世界

464
00:23:37,784 --> 00:23:41,989
今晚在座的是吉姆・哈克阁下
our Man ontheSpot tonightis the Right HonourableJim Hacker,

